It's time to give the bedroom a thorough makeover. This is the last room in the house that has only done simple decoration.
Remove the ugly wall heaters and furnace. Seal up the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Customise a wardrobe.
We usually draw a rough pencil sketch first……
The messy phase is over.
Found a few dead birds behind the chimney, their bodies all dry :((
Prepare to welcome the plastering work next week
I'm quite satisfied with the small alcove next to it
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing yet 🙈)
Haha, look what we found behind the heaters!
Do you remember adding the cute ventilation holes to prevent the chimney from getting damp?
Sweep 把烟囱盖和烟囱帽都装好了。那些喜欢在烟囱里筑巢的白嘴鸦以后应该会更安全了🪺
抹灰工完工了。我们明天铺地板！
软木垫已经铺设完毕，还用卫生纸卷筒给吸尘器做了个配件，用来吸锯末。😂
部分地板已经整理好，可以开始铺设了。我们先喝杯茶休息一下。
嗯，今天进度有点慢，因为为了和走廊（也正在铺设地板）无缝衔接，需要在门框周围进行切割，操作起来很费劲。@user45@twitter.com 一直在抱怨我
We're finally done, but it's a mess! And what's even crazier is that the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. I can finally sleep well tonight!
There's still the hallway flooring and the baseboard left. The decoration workers are coming a month later, so we can only make do with what we have for now, and the room is just bare plaster.
I'm going to do some simple DIY tonight. I'll use a coping saw and a chisel to cut out the bottom of the doorframe a bit, so the floor can be perfectly laid underneath.
The underlayment for the hallway floor is also done
Yesterday we were able to finish laying the hallway floor! I woke up at 5 am this morning to go to Heathrow Airport to pick up Package 1, and then I took a nap and finally I can start installing the baseboard for the hallway. I'll fill in the gaps after the glue dries.
